name: Day of the Dead 2024
summary: Dia de los Muertos, or Day of the Dead, is a Mexican holiday that celebrates the deceased. It is a time for families and friends to gather and remember their loved ones who have passed away. The holiday is observed on November 1st and 2nd, and in 2024, it will fall on a Friday and Saturday. There are many ways to celebrate Day of the Dead, including visiting cemeteries, building altars to honor the dead, and eating traditional foods such as tamales and pan de muerto. Dia de los Muertos is a vibrant and colorful holiday that celebrates life and death. It is a time to remember and honor those who have passed away, and to celebrate the beauty of life.

name: All Saints' Day 2024
summary: Following the festivities of Halloween, Christians commemorate All Saints' Day, a day dedicated to remembering and honoring the saints who have passed away. It is celebrated in conjunction with All Souls' Day, which focuses on praying for the souls of the departed. Masses and special services are held in churches to pay tribute to the saints and their exemplary lives. Some celebrations involve parades or processions featuring children dressed as saints. Additionally, families visit cemeteries to decorate graves and offer prayers for their loved ones. The observance of All Saints' Day serves as a time for spiritual reflection, remembrance, and the celebration of those who have lived virtuous and inspiring lives.

name: Hugh Hewitt
summary: Right-wing commentator Hugh Hewitt has resigned from his position as a columnist for the Washington Post. The move comes after Hewitt abruptly stormed off the set of a live Post interview with liberal colleagues. Hewitt, a staunch Trump supporter, took issue with an advertisement for a Democratic congressional candidate that aired during the show. He characterized the ad as "the most unfair election ad" he had ever seen and declared, "I'm done." This incident has sparked significant backlash and scrutiny of Hewitt's actions, with many criticizing his unprofessionalism and inability to engage in civil discourse.
